New version with all 6 outfits: hoodie, neko, atlantis, kimono, red alter ego, and bikini. As well as a generic "gawr gura" tag for all your other needs.

Observations:

  • Correction: The activation tag for the hoodie outfit is also "gawr gura".

  • Use at weight 1, it's slightly overcooked but the face and teeth get fixed with hires fix.

  • You need very few tags for each outfit to work, check the tags to the right side. But you can still use more tags such as: shark tail, sharp teeth, trident, shoulder bag (neko outfit), black hoodie (red outfit), two side up (default outfit), barefoot/sandals, shark/cube hair ornament, etc.

  • The bikini is the popular but unofficial shark print bikini, one cup should be red with teeth.

Made using my Lora guide.

I put a lot of effort into my Loras, if you like my work consider leaving me a tip :)

This model is also available on tensor.art

items.name: Autumn Arboretum
items.description:
While even the default SD 1.5 generates very nice trees - I couldn't find a way to generate exactly the style I was looking for. Hence I created this LoRA - it's nothing sophisticated, just a simple LoRA trained on 50 high quality photos taken by my girlfriend in the Rogowo Arboretum in late October. Trees were yellow and red, sky was blue, sun was shining.

Use it to generate nice delicate colorful trees or leaves. While it was trained on the images of trees and leaves only - it's also good for backgrounds too for all your mythical animals, witches, wood elves or other chineese cartoon underage girls with overgrown breasts.

rogowoarboretum is the trigger word, use additional keywords like "red leaves", "yellow leaves", "yellow trees", "red trees", "pink flowers", "red berries", "red fruit", "park bench", "woods", "forest", "close up" and so on.

LoRA weight of 0.8 or lower.

items.name: Mercy (Overwatch) LORA
items.description:
My tenth Overwatch LORA. Original appearance + Witch + a bit of Doctor. This one is quite flexible and modular, add what you want as you see fit in both positives and negatives.

  • Main trigger\Face - mercy, high ponytail, hair tie

  • Original outfit - mechanical halo, bodysuit, long sleeves, gloves, loincloth, brown legwear, armored boots

  • Witch outfit - witch, witch costume, witch hat, book on belt

  • Wings - mechanical wings, for spread out yellow ones use yellow wings, glowing wings instead, use no wings to remove them if they appear on their own.

  • Miscellaneous - labcoat, name tag, periscope, glowing, holding staff, hair over one eye, short hair

Checked strength range is 0.5-0.9, more weight - more Overwatch style bleeds in.
If you liked my work, you can donate here.

Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.

Trained on Anything V4.5 with anime.vae.pt and CLIP Skip 2.

Samples are 512x768, without HighRes.fix, using OrangeCocoa 50/50 Mix , with OrangeMix VAE, and using EasyNegative embedding, CLIP Skip 2.

items.name: Blessed Naoto Shirogane Lora
items.description:
Training models is completely free and costs me absolutely nothing. You can support me by writing me positive reviews. :P

This is the sixth version of the model, I put a lot of work into this for a week until it was good. Trained with the extra legal version of stable diffusion.
Tags:
Character tag - Naoto Shirogane (P4)
Signature hat - cabbie hat
Dancing night outfit - naotodancing
Yasogami school uniform - naotostudent
Detective uniform - naotodetective
Reverse trap - androgynous

The outfits need some extra tagging and a bit of luck to get them to be consistent, the yasogami uniform doesnt work very well sadly. Sub tags id recommend for the outfit tags:
naotodancing - blue shirt, suspenders, yellow necktie, black pants, fingerless gloves,
naotostudent - school uniform, black pants, white collared shirt, black jacket,
naotodetective - detective uniform, blue coat, white trimmed coat, plaid pants,
androgynous - Negative tag: (breasts)

She has two canon eye colors, grey and blue. You can tag which you want. As she's a reverse trap if you dont use the 1girl tag it might draw her as a male with abs. Used a pose/concept lora in 2 of the preview images. Check preview tags for outfit tag examples, nsfw at the end. ((nude)) recommended for full nudity as her outfits will likely pop up

items.name: Greenmageddon
items.description:
This has been trained on macro photos of lichens and moss that I once took. My intention was to use it as style modifier. Created with Invoke-AI. It works for me with some models and with some it does not, so there's room to experiment. I had good results with realistic/general models, e.g. Deliberate and it works great with iCoMix, which is comic style biased merge.

Use style token alone and it will generate fantasy macros of alien looking lichens. The fun is in mixing it with prompt which requires finding right weight balance. So this is not a ready-made, but requires a lot of tinkering. Here's my approach...

First of all, 'quality' keywords are not really needed and do not make much sense. Depth of field concept is imprinted in the style, as the photos all had a lot of it, so you may want to counter it with negative prompt. Other that that, I would just leave negative part alone.

I would start with defining weights for style and the rest of the prompt, which would look like that (using invoke-ai syntax, but I'm sure you will figure how does it translate, same with prompts on example images):

(<stardeaf-greenmageddon>)0.8, (sleepy zombie reading a paper, raining)0.8

Then I would adjust weights until I find a sweet spot that blends both in an interesting way. The right ratio depends on model, prompt and image size, so experiment... For me odd, detailed ratios seem to work best, like 0.55:0.67. When you get just lichen vegetation, take weight out of style side. I also keep cfg and steps low (below 5 for cfg, step in range of 9-18.)

iCoMix model is here:

https://civitai.com/models/16164

Taking the experiment further, I made derivatives of the embedding. These were trained on images created by using the original style with iCoMix model, as I wanted to see how will they perform when used in other, realistic models...

So the other versions are not updates but derivatives, each with it's own mood. Again, use token weighting to add twirliness and alien organic feel to your image.

Have fun.

items.name: StrixMix
items.description:
A personal mix I made which I felt good enough to share! My own testing has shown it to be quite versatile, generally accepting of LoRAs, and it does pretty good hands out the box!

Multiple furry models were used in the merge, and it sometimes shows through on human subjects in the form of things like cat ears. Adding "animal ears" to your negative will usually suppress this. It is, however, very good at anthro subjects.

AOM2 was also used in the merge, so if you dislike its signature "M" hair adding "hair between eyes" with some added weight generally helps greatly.

Recommended Settings:

Clip Skip: 1 or 2 (Examples use 1)

Steps: 20+, ~50 is my normal.

CFG: 3.5 (Higher CFG gives more vibrant color, lower will quickly destabilize.)

Upscaler: 4x_fatal_Anime_500000_G

VAE: kl-f8-anime2

items.name: 【Art Style】Ban! Style
items.description:
Introduction

A LoRA model trained with ~200 images by Ban!. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.5 version YesMix.

Cautions (Must Read)

  • Some preview images are generated using hires fix. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024 theoretically, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Huntress - Risk of Rain
items.description:
The Huntress! She's got more crowbars than Gordon Freeman...

This is a lora trained on 131 hand picked images of the Huntress from Risk of Rain. It was mostly trained on digital art, but there is a smidgeon of 3d art also. It gets the helmet pretty good, but sometimes forgets an antenna, and will put two light things on the chestplate. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5, I used it for all of the example images.

NOTES:

-She has 3 little inconsistent bits: Her chest light thing, her antennas, and her scarf. Usually they all behave pretty well, but it can be a little odd at lower weights. Her antenna is probably more consistent if you prompt it (I forgot to do this on ALL my example images :P)

-Despite everything, it can't generate her bow pretty much at all. I might train a "holding bow" lora in the future...

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)

Check out my Artificer model here: https://civitai.com/models/20139/artificer-risk-of-rain

Happy St Patrick's Day! Caoimhe is the third in a new set of custom LastName characters, for anyone who wants a consistent character for their SD 1.5 renders.

Caoimhe is Irish. Her name is pronounced "Quee-vah". (For reals.) She might be a princess, an elf, a fairy, a warrior, or a mermaid. She might be a stereotype. Either way, she's definitely beautiful. If she smiles at you, it's over.

Note: The redness of Caoimhe's hair depends on the time of day. If in doubt, add long red hair to your prompt to be sure.

To use this embedding with the Automatic1111 web UI, save the downloaded file to /embeddings/caoimhelastnamesd15.pt, and then include the trigger word caoimhelastnamesd15 in your prompt.

(Inspired by Zovya's Nobody series, which is awesome. Go download all of their amazing characters.)

items.name: Inuyasha - LoRA
items.description:
This is my first published LoRA, I tried to use all kinds of sources for the data set so you don't only get the carbon copy of the character. As seen in the examples it kind of works most of the time on semi realistic checkpoints and can be genderbended easily retaining clothes, hair, etc.

If you would like a more closer to anime look, use official style in your prompts. If he loses any of his characteristics you can help him restore them with: long hair ,white hair,dog ears,yellow eyes,red kimono,etc. I recommend to use him at 0.6~0.8, but 1 is fine although the anime style will take over.

I'll probably keep making more characters and other kinds of LoRAs, if you want to support me, you can go to my wife's DA where she has a subscription and is the same as me having a kofi or similar.

items.name: Audrey Hepburn/奥黛丽 · 赫本
items.description:
• 本次模型的主题是奥黛丽 · 赫本，训练基于chilloutmix模型，共计使用了117张赫本的图像，包含彩色与黑白不同种类，主要以面部为主，所有照片来源均来自网络，每张照片均进行10次运算，最终得出LoRA模型。展示图基础模型为：chilloutmix，VAE为：vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned，因为训练图大多为面部，所以上半身照片更合适，如果产出图片显示人物消瘦明显，可以适当补充tag完善。

  • The theme of this model is Audrey Hepburn. It was trained on the chilloutmix model using a total of 117 images of Hepburn, including both color and black-and-white images, mainly focused on her face. All images were sourced from the internet and underwent 10 iterations each. The final result was the LoRA model. The base model used for display is chilloutmix, while the VAE used is vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned. As most of the training images focused on the face, upper body photos were more suitable for display.If the output picture shows that the character is obviously emaciated, tag can be supplemented appropriately.

items.name: Celty Sturluson - Durarara!!
items.description:
Celty Sturluson from the anime Durarara!! - Full disclosure, I've never seen this anime, but I loved her design, and... here we are!

This is a lora trained on 87 hand picked images (and 1 gif by accident lol) of Celty from Durarara!! It was exclusively trained on digital art, no 3d content. It gets the helmet pretty good along with her suit, mostly because her design is pretty simple besides the helmet. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5, I used it for most of the example images.

NOTES:

-The helmet could be removed if you prompt no helmet and define the facial features, and lower the weight... But why would you do that?!

-It will still have issues generating vehicles/motorbikes, but it can still kind of work on some models if you're lucky

-It can generate a "male" version of this character with the right prompting

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)
